holomew","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Barthélémy De Vignory was born about 1141, in France, his father, Guy De Vignory V, was 19 and his mother, Mrs. Tiphaine Vignory, was 22. He married Elvide de Brienne. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1191, in Acre, Northern, Palestine, at the age of 51."},"et":{"abt 1141–1191":"umbes 1141–1191","1141–1191":"1141–1191","1145–1165":"1145–1165","1135–1199":"1135–1199","1162–1207":"1162–1207","1170–1228":"1170–1228","–1229":"–1229","1124–1150":"1124–1150","1120–1145":"1120–1145","AFT 1145":"pärast 1145","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","abt 1141":"umbes 1141","1141":"1141","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1191":"1191","1228":"1228","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","AFT 1150":"pärast 1150","1229":"1229","1207":"1207","Acre, Palestine (Now Holy Land, Akko Hazafon, Israel)":"Acre, Northern, Palestiina","France":"Prantsusmaa","Uxelles, Jura, Franche-Comté, France":"Uxelles, Jura, Franche-Comté, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"abt 1141–1191":"noin 1141–1191","1141–1191":"1141–1191","1145–1165":"1145–1165","1135–1199":"1135–1199","1162–1207":"1162–1207","1170–1228":"1170–1228","–1229":"–1229","1124–1150":"1124–1150","1120–1145":"1120–1145","AFT 1145":"1145 jälkeen","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","abt 1141":"noin 1141","1141":"1141","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1191":"1191","1228":"1228","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","AFT 1150":"1150 jälkeen","1229":"1229","1207":"1207","Acre, Palestine (Now Holy Land, Akko Hazafon, Israel)":"Acre, Northern, Palestiina","France":"Ranska","Uxelles, Ju